    <string name="settings_service_upstream_help">Main upstream interface regex used to reroute downstream traffic. VPN Hotspot itself must be allowed to use that VPN to work. Use &lt;tt&gt;none&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;a^&lt;/tt&gt;, or another invalid regex to suppress tethering through VPN.</string>
    <string name="settings_upstream_fallback_help">Fallback upstream is used when a VPN leaves some routes on the default network. Use &lt;tt&gt;none&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;a^&lt;/tt&gt;, or another invalid regex to forbid fallback.</string>
    <string name="settings_service_masquerade_none_summary">Do not rewrite downstream source addresses or ports. This can work better with dummy VPNs such as ad blockers or socksifiers, but should not be used with real VPNs.</string>
    <string name="settings_service_masquerade_simple_summary">Rewrite downstream source addresses and ports in app-owned routing rules.</string>
    <string name="settings_service_masquerade_netd_summary">Ask Android &lt;tt&gt;netd&lt;/tt&gt; to handle masquerade. Android may add platform extras such as &lt;tt&gt;FTP&lt;/tt&gt; handling and tethering counters, but this is a poor fit when hiding tethering activity from the carrier.</string>
    <string name="settings_service_ipv6_mode_system_summary">Leave IPv6 handling to the platform routing setup.</string>
    <string name="settings_service_ipv6_mode_block_summary">Prevent IPv6 leaks on downstream interfaces.</string>
    <string name="settings_service_ipv6_mode_nat_summary">Assign a deterministic app-owned ULA &lt;tt&gt;/64&lt;/tt&gt; and proxy downstream IPv6 &lt;tt&gt;TCP&lt;/tt&gt;/&lt;tt&gt;UDP&lt;/tt&gt; plus best-effort &lt;tt&gt;ICMPv6&lt;/tt&gt; through the root daemon. This is userspace work, not full packet NAT, and it does not forward arbitrary IPv6 next-header protocols.</string>
